Search in twitter database for 2000 tweets

tweets1 <- searchTwitter("datascience", n = 2000, lang = "en")

Extract specific information from all harvested Tweets and Cleaning Data

tweets.text <- sapply(tweets1, function(x) x$getText())
tweets.text <- sapply(tweets.text, function(x) str_replace_all(x, "[[:punct:]]", " "))

Interpreting each element of the vector as documemt and Creating List of documents

tweets.corpus <- Corpus(VectorSource(tweets.text)) # create a corpus

Creating a Matrix Documents designated as rows words in columns Each elements are counts/weights(tf-idf)

term.doc.matrix <- TermDocumentMatrix(
  tweets.corpus,
  control = list(
    removePunctuation = TRUE,
    stopwords = c("datascience", "https", "http", stopwords("english")),
    removeNumbers = TRUE,
    tolower = TRUE
  )
)

Sorting the words with most frequency

term.doc.matrix <- as.matrix(term.doc.matrix)
word.freqs <- sort(rowSums(term.doc.matrix), decreasing = TRUE)
dm <- data.frame(word = names(word.freqs), freq = word.freqs)

Graphically represent Frequently used words in collection of the text files

          dm$freq,
          random.order = FALSE,
          colors = brewer.pal(8, "Dark2"))
